Deputy Minister in the Department of Cooperative Government and Traditional Affairs, Andries Nel says through the municipal infrastructure support agent, they have been working very intensely with the bottom third municipalities that lack the capacity to render basic services, to assist them out of the distress state where they can get the basic’s right. They are working together with other national departments and provincial treasuries to do further diagnosis of the problems in those municipalities and to develop recovery plans. However, he says they need to be focused on the capacity that they have so to build sustainability. On Monday, The Minister of Cooperative Government and Traditional Affairs, Zweli Mkhize announced that only 7% of the country’s municipalities are classified as well-functioning, with 31% being reasonably functional, 31% almost dysfunctional while the remaining 31% is dysfunctional. Watch the full interview:   